      {
        "id": 2084304,
        "name": "Daniel Kim",
        "username": "Daniel_Kim",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/90db22/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-12-23T03:27:19.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I would also add that the addition of Vioginer, Marsanne and Roussanne can help soften tannins and add texture.</p>\n<p>While it\u2019s common enough to co-ferment Viognier from the Cote Blonde and lieux-dits closer to Condrieu, wines made from the Northern slope of Cote Rotie such as Cote Brune are usually 100% Syrah.</p>\n<p>It\u2019s pretty rare for producers in Hermitage to co-ferment. Can\u2019t think of anyone off the top of my head that does it intentionally.</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 11,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T20:53:51.542Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
